<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-12-27T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-12-27T13:00:00-05:00" n="875" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d875">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">833.5151/557: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reed</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-12-27T15:00:00-03:00">December 27, 1938—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 27—1:31 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>116. December import quotas for controlled exchange just announced total
                            303,000 pounds sterling. They include 12 countries but exclude not only
                            the United States but also Great Britain. Germany obtains largest quota,
                            100,000 pounds.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Reed</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>